The paper discusses the misuse of social media and instant messaging services for cybercrimes, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The investigation and analysis of these services in Firefox OS involves examining residual remnants, which could be related to digital forensics (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the importance of mobile devices in digital investigation, which could be related to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The analysis of user communication and behavior on social media and instant messaging services could also be related to software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
